The three configurations in Table~\ref{tab:phase1} differ in both the type and the number of admitted trials (80, 3{,}240, 12{,}960). The median null residual decreases with trial count as expected under any null where more trials produce a tighter best-trial distribution. We do not attempt to disentangle the causal contribution of non-self-scale running from the multiplicity that running introduces; a matched-complexity comparison (equal trial counts with different compositions) would be required to identify running's independent contribution to the noise floor. What Table~\ref{tab:phase1} does show is that the observed best residual is typical under the matched null in each configuration: admitting the freedom to run masses to non-self scales does not move the observed closure into the tail of the null distribution generated by that same freedom.

